525
00:43:27,150 --> 00:43:30,880
Chairman Ju, if we find him, we can find Min Seol Ah's phone—

526
00:43:30,880 --> 00:43:35,550
You little—  Shut up your mouth, seriously!

527
00:43:35,550 --> 00:43:40,080
Then why have you been holding on to her phone for this long, creating this mess?

528
00:43:42,530 --> 00:43:44,290
Chairman.

529
00:43:47,150 --> 00:43:49,370
L-Lawyer Lee?

530
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:54,620
So our redevelopment plan—

531
00:43:54,620 --> 00:43:57,740
- What's wrong? 
 - I just got off the phone with Logan Lee.

532
00:43:57,740 --> 00:44:00,260
He's on his way to the hotel.

533
00:44:00,260 --> 00:44:03,470
Have the car ready.  Oh Yun Hui will go with us.

534
00:44:58,270 --> 00:45:01,200
What are you doing? How did you get in here?

535
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:04,970
It was you? Seol Ah's adopted brother?

536
00:45:04,970 --> 00:45:09,360
You did such cruel things to my daughter, yet you dare to threaten me? Using Seol Ah's name?

537
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:11,910
You adopted my Seol Ah to take her bone marrow, didn't you?

538
00:45:11,910 --> 00:45:14,650
And then frame her for robbery and cancel the adoption?

539
00:45:14,650 --> 00:45:16,670
You should have just thrown her out!

540
00:45:16,670 --> 00:45:19,630
Why did you give scars to the poor child?

541
00:45:19,630 --> 00:45:21,870
I didn't know.

542
00:45:21,870 --> 00:45:26,700
I found out the truth later. And I wanted to take responsibility somehow.

543
00:45:26,700 --> 00:45:30,870
But Seol Ah... died.

544
00:45:30,870 --> 00:45:33,870
How much was the deal with Assemblyman Jo Sang Heon?

545
00:45:33,870 --> 00:45:36,410
Do you know how long I looked for you?

546
00:45:36,410 --> 00:45:39,550
You hid so well using your rich family.

547
00:45:39,550 --> 00:45:41,340
Why did you appear now?

548
00:45:42,490 --> 00:45:47,410
If you lived because of that young girl, then you should've lived like a human!

549
00:45:47,410 --> 00:45:50,310
You're not even human!

550
00:45:50,400 --> 00:45:54,100
So I came! Even though I'm inhumane,

551
00:45:54,150 --> 00:45:57,070
I wanted to live unashamed for once.

552
00:45:57,930 --> 00:46:01,350
You bastard, are you going to weasel out until the end?

553
00:46:01,350 --> 00:46:04,880
I promised myself everyday that I would kill you.

554
00:46:04,880 --> 00:46:07,830
Die, die, die, die!

555
00:46:07,900 --> 00:46:09,100
Die!

556
00:46:11,300 --> 00:46:12,400
Stop it now.

557
00:46:12,450 --> 00:46:15,180
Stop, stop! Stop!

558
00:46:15,180 --> 00:46:19,110
Stop it. Stop it!

559
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:21,460
I understand.

560
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:23,540
So stop.

561
00:46:28,960 --> 00:46:32,790
Ok, kill me.

562
00:46:43,660 --> 00:46:48,000
But before that, kill Ju Dan Tae first.

563
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:54,480
Why? You can't give up that petty family of yours?

564
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:58,880
Even if Ju Dan Tae killed your daughter? Because he's your husband?

565
00:46:58,880 --> 00:47:04,010
Shut up. I'll kill Ju Dan Tae and Cheon Seo Jin. And you as well.

566
00:47:04,010 --> 00:47:07,530
You have to find out the culprit who killed Seol Ah first.

567
00:47:08,460 --> 00:47:12,660
Before that. I'll give you a chance.

568
00:47:12,660 --> 00:47:17,010
A chance to act like a mom for once.

569
00:47:22,570 --> 00:47:27,960
  Oppa, you said you would find me my mom, right? 

570
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:32,240
  There's something I want to check. I want to see how she's living. 

571
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:34,470
  How do you wish she's living? 

572
00:47:34,470 --> 00:47:37,880
  I wish mom was living as miserably as I am. 

573
00:47:39,770 --> 00:47:43,690
  When I was young, I used to think like that. 

574
00:47:43,700 --> 00:47:47,600
  But not anymore. I ... 

575
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:52,920
  I want mom to be really happy. 

576
00:47:55,290 --> 00:47:58,540
  I want her to live very happily. 

577
00:48:02,930 --> 00:48:04,580
Seol Ah...

578
00:48:04,580 --> 00:48:09,110
  Oppa. Find my mom, 

579
00:48:09,110 --> 00:48:12,550
  and check if she's living happily. 

580
00:48:12,550 --> 00:48:14,190
  Then I'll... 

581
00:48:16,670 --> 00:48:19,650
  be ok even if I never meet her. 

582
00:48:24,850 --> 00:48:27,890
I don't have any right to be happy.

583
00:48:38,110 --> 00:48:41,760
Let's do it together. Seol Ah's revenge.

584
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:45,910
I'll take my punishment after.

585
00:48:45,910 --> 00:48:47,960
I have no thoughts on taking your side.

586
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:52,400
No, just like I misunderstood you, you misunderstood me.

587
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:56,550
We... have the same goal.

588
00:48:56,600 --> 00:49:00,500
You don't have any right. You should've taken responsibility for her.

589
00:49:00,500 --> 00:49:03,620
You should've protected her no matter what!

590
00:49:04,330 --> 00:49:06,110
I don't want to make excuses.

591
00:49:06,110 --> 00:49:09,990
But I know a way to repay her. That's why I'm looking for the person who killed her!

592
00:49:09,990 --> 00:49:13,860
I'll find them. And punish them ten millions times over.!

593
00:49:15,260 --> 00:49:17,050
I will punish them that many times more painfully.

594
00:49:17,050 --> 00:49:20,630
No. I don't trust you.

595
00:49:20,630 --> 00:49:23,330
I risked my life for this.

596
00:49:23,330 --> 00:49:27,500
I'm going to solve my Seol Ah's wrongful death.

597
00:49:28,450 --> 00:49:31,470
I'm going to get rid of anyone in my path.

598
00:49:57,090 --> 00:50:01,200
What are you doing here?

599
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:04,900
I'm asking!

600
00:50:04,900 --> 00:50:08,260
Why are you coming out of Logan Lee's room?

601
00:50:19,580 --> 00:50:23,090
Could you explain what's going on, Logan?

602
00:50:23,930 --> 00:50:28,480
Why is my wife coming out of your room?

603
00:50:29,650 --> 00:50:33,350
You have a very admirable wife, Mr. Ju.

604
00:50:34,870 --> 00:50:38,200
What is that supposed to mean?

605
00:50:38,200 --> 00:50:40,840
Well, to be honest,

606
00:50:40,840 --> 00:50:43,790
because of the unfortunate event last night,

607
00:50:43,790 --> 00:50:47,570
I was actually thinking about cancelling our contract.

608
00:50:47,570 --> 00:50:50,290
But that was before your wife came in,

609
00:50:50,290 --> 00:50:53,890
and apologized, for you instead.

610
00:50:55,790 --> 00:50:58,060
This is what they call the wife's support.

611
00:50:58,060 --> 00:51:01,430
Su Ryeon did a big job.

612
00:51:01,430 --> 00:51:04,900
I was very touched by our conversation tonight.

613
00:51:04,900 --> 00:51:08,830
I'll take a step back, and make a reconsideration.

614
00:51:09,450 --> 00:51:11,770
I appreciate it.

615
00:51:11,770 --> 00:51:14,470
We look forward to hearing from you soon.

616
00:51:22,530 --> 00:51:25,800
To be honest, do you think we lent the money trusting Ha Yun Cheol?

617
00:51:25,800 --> 00:51:28,370
We lent it because we trust you, Seo Jin.

618
00:51:28,370 --> 00:51:31,880
We thought there would be no way that the daughter of Cheong Ah Foundation would not pay back our money.

619
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:35,470
I don't know about that money. This is the first time I heard about it.

620
00:51:35,470 --> 00:51:38,250
That doesn't mean you have no responsibility.

621
00:51:38,250 --> 00:51:40,300
You are a married couple anyway.

622
00:51:45,140 --> 00:51:48,520
Why did you come here? If you have something to say, say it to me.

623
00:51:48,520 --> 00:51:52,000
Hey. You were ignoring my calls.

624
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:54,590
Get out! I'll contact you later.

625
00:51:57,100 --> 00:51:59,500
You as a doctor, why are you acting so lowly?

626
00:51:59,500 --> 00:52:02,790
Repay me my money instantly, you conman!

627
00:52:02,790 --> 00:52:06,500
Who's a conman? Why did you lend him money if you thought he was a conman?

628
00:52:06,500 --> 00:52:08,100
I thought you were his hometown friends,

629
00:52:08,100 --> 00:52:10,300
but is 5% interest reasonable? Why?

630
00:52:10,300 --> 00:52:12,100
Were you trying to make yourself rich by extorting from your friend?

631
00:52:12,100 --> 00:52:13,600
- Look at me! 
 - What do I look at?

632
00:52:13,700 --> 00:52:16,280
Did you lend me your money? Why do you speak informally?

633
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:19,310
Don't make a scene at someone else's school, get lost right now.

634
00:52:20,380 --> 00:52:22,220
Do you want to be dragged out?

635
00:52:22,220 --> 00:52:24,040
We can't wait long.

636
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:27,990
Next time, we'll come back ready to stay with blankets whether it's in  the school or in the hospital.

637
00:52:36,020 --> 00:52:37,840
Ha Yun Cheol.

638
00:52:39,030 --> 00:52:42,250
You're gotten more courageous after living with me.

639
00:52:42,250 --> 00:52:46,050
What did you do with that money. Did you start a business?

640
00:52:46,050 --> 00:52:50,730
Or did one of your aunts cause trouble again?

641
00:52:50,730 --> 00:52:53,990
None of your concern. I'll take care of it on my own.

642
00:52:53,990 --> 00:52:57,450
I heard it was 7 billion won (about  $7 million) that you took from your friends' pockets.

643
00:52:57,450 --> 00:53:00,800
How will you be able to repay that with your skills?

644
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:08,120
I'll take care of it for you.

645
00:53:10,620 --> 00:53:12,860
It's your divorce alimony.

646
00:53:12,860 --> 00:53:16,140
In return, the custody of Eun Byeol, the house,

647
00:53:16,140 --> 00:53:19,060
our combined wealth, and the director position for Cheong Ah Medical center, give up all of them.

648
00:53:19,100 --> 00:53:24,600
One more. Until I become Chairman, agree to cooperate.

649
00:53:24,710 --> 00:53:28,830
Then I'll take on your debt.

650
00:53:28,830 --> 00:53:33,120
You want to erase your wrongdoings with 7 billion won?

651
00:53:39,900 --> 00:53:41,760
My wrong doings?

652
00:53:42,850 --> 00:53:44,980
You sound like a husband.

653
00:53:44,980 --> 00:53:46,980
Were we ever a married couple?

654
00:53:46,980 --> 00:53:49,640
It's been over 10 years since we slept together.

655
00:53:49,640 --> 00:53:53,570
I've never received money or love from you.

656
00:53:55,700 --> 00:54:01,100
How are you going to compensate me for my misfortune?

657
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:06,520
Correctly speaking, you're the reason our marriage started falling apart.

658
00:54:06,520 --> 00:54:09,500
For 17 years,

659
00:54:11,840 --> 00:54:17,160
I've always been lonely. And I've never received a paycheck from you.

660
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:20,410
You've never cared or looked after me,

661
00:54:20,410 --> 00:54:23,570
but now you want me to accept responsibility for hurting you?

662
00:54:23,570 --> 00:54:27,540
The reason I'm seeing another man is because of you!

663
00:54:27,540 --> 00:54:30,400
But I'm still offering you 7 billion won in alimony.

664
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,370
Isn't that appealing to you?

665
00:54:32,370 --> 00:54:35,530
Is the selfishness of knowing only yourself an incurable disease?

666
00:54:35,530 --> 00:54:39,720
There's no way. Things won't go the way you want it to.

667
00:54:50,660 --> 00:54:52,750
Will it really not?

668
00:55:01,710 --> 00:55:04,400
Open it. It's a gift.

669
00:55:09,980 --> 00:55:12,270
I heard this is popular right now.

670
00:55:12,270 --> 00:55:15,570
You're probably stressing out preparing for the midterms.

671
00:55:15,570 --> 00:55:18,360
I got this so you can find some strength.

672
00:55:18,360 --> 00:55:20,440
What do you think? Isn't it pretty?

673
00:55:22,580 --> 00:55:27,210
Why, you don't like it? Do you want to exchange it for a different one?

674
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:38,020
Who said I wanted this?

675
00:55:39,590 --> 00:55:42,530
Who said I needed a  luxury wallet?

676
00:55:42,530 --> 00:55:46,200
Bae Ro Na. What are you doing right now?

677
00:55:46,200 --> 00:55:47,990
I'm so sick of it.

678
00:55:47,990 --> 00:55:50,440
Why of all places did we come to Hera Palace?

679
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:53,120
It's so annoying.

680
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:58,500
Why is she acting like that?

681
00:56:03,350 --> 00:56:06,430
Don't worry Mom, I'll do it.

682
00:56:07,410 --> 00:56:09,090
It's no big deal.

683
00:56:09,090 --> 00:56:12,600
I'll resolve it soon, bye.

684
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:15,610
The creditors must've gone to the orchard.

685
00:56:15,610 --> 00:56:19,050
Your parents must be very worried.

686
00:56:19,050 --> 00:56:22,460
That's why you shouldn't use someone else's money recklessly.

687
00:56:23,950 --> 00:56:28,240
Give my suggestion some thought. The conditions are not bad.

688
00:56:28,240 --> 00:56:31,520
I'll keep it a secret from Eun Byeol for the time being.

689
00:56:31,520 --> 00:56:35,530
Since if she gets shocked, it can interfere with her studies.

690
00:56:35,530 --> 00:56:37,680
Sign our divorce documents.

